All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
AbstractTestPlan
Abstract class for different kinds of TestPlans.
FailingTestList
Extends AbstractTestPlan and holds the failing test cases for all projects currently available in the system
ILog<E>
Represents as list where elements can only be added to the end of the list.
ISortedList<E extends Comparable<E>>
Interface for a list that keeps objects in sorted order as defined by the Comparable interface.
ISwapList<E>
Interface for a list that changes the position of elements through swap operations.
Log<E>
An Array based list that maintains a log of information.
SortedList<E extends Comparable<E>>
Implements the ISortedList interface that represents a list that keeps objects in sorted order as defined by the Comparable interface.
SwapList<E>
Implements the ISwapList interface that represents a list that changes the position of elements through swap operations.
SystemTestPlanGUI
User Interface for the SystemTestPlan project that provides the user the ability to interact with test plans, tests, and their results.
TestCase
Class that contains the information about each individual test case including the testCaseId, testType, testDescription, expectedResults, and Ilog of TestResults
TestPlan
The TestPlan class manages a list of TestCases, adding them, returning them, and comparing them.
TestPlanManager
TestPlanManager contains a list of TestPlans, the FailingTestList, and the operations needed to manipulate these lists as well as the test cases and test results contained in them.
TestPlanReader
Processes a file containing test plans with zero to many test cases each with zero to many results The format for the file should look like this: ! (Test plan name) # (Test case name), (Test case type) * (Test Description) //may contain multiple lines, if so they will be numbered: 1.
TestPlanWriter
Contains static method for writing TestPlans to files.
TestResult
Class that contains the information about the results of a single execution of a TestCase.
